    "path": "src/tool/native/file",
    "name": "file",
    "purpose": "Filesystem native tool programs. Each file defines one unit-struct tool that carries NAME/DESCRIPTION/INPUT_SCHEMA/OUTPUT_SCHEMA constants and implements ToolProgram: read_file.rs (ReadFile), write_file.rs (WriteFile), list_directory.rs (ListDirectory), and search_text.rs (SearchText). preview() still builds a ToolPreview from the constants, and invoke() is now implemented (no longer a panic stub): it parses the JSON call via marix_common::external::serde_json (Value/from_str/json/to_string), performs the filesystem work, and returns a JSON result string, falling back to a {\"error\":..} JSON built by a file-local private failure helper on any failure. ReadFile reads {path} into {content} via std::fs::read_to_string; WriteFile writes {path, content, create_dirs?} (optionally std::fs::create_dir_all the parent) via std::fs::write and returns {bytes_written}; ListDirectory reads {path, recursive?} and returns {entries:[paths]} using a private recursive collect_entries helper; SearchText reads {path, query, case_sensitive?} and returns {matches:[{path,line,text}]} using a private recursive search_path helper that skips unreadable files. mod.rs is re-export wiring only.",
